HEADWORD: Etherization
<hw>E`ther*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The administration of ether to produce
insensibility.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The state of the system under the
influence of ether.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

